<p>Consider the following operation on an arbitrary <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Positive_integer" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Positive=
 integer">positive integer</a>:
</p>
<ul><li>If the number is even, divide it by two.</li>
<li>If the number is odd, triple it and add one.</li></ul>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_arithmetic" title=3D=
"Modular arithmetic">modular arithmetic</a> notation, define the <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Function_(mathematics)" title=3D"Function (m=
athematics)">function</a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">f</span> as follows:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
