n></span>, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sub>0</sub> =3D 0</span>, <span=
 class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i><sub>1</sub> =3D 3</span>, <span class=3D"texhtm=
l"><i>b</i><sub>1</sub> =3D 1</span>. Conway proved that the problem
</p>
<dl><dd>Given <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">g</=
span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span=
>, does the sequence of iterates <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>g<sup>k</sup></=
